page.title: 06King's Lynn Docks
page.content: The Alexandra and Bentinck docks are situated close to the Wash at King's Lynn. It began its first containerised liner service in 1983. The Bentinck dock is also served by rail and is therefore capable of handling Freightliner traffic. {Imports}-timber from Russia,Finland and other Scandinavian countries motor vehicles and parts(Skoda) Zetor tractors combine harvesters and other heavy agricultural machinery petroleum and chemicals fertilizer and animal feed grain-rice,maize {Exports}-Scrap metal to European and Far East markets grain-wheat,barley steel The docks can take ships of 88 metres.
